# Skateboard Rental Web Application - Project Specification

## 1. Project Overview

### 1.1 Purpose
Design and develop a web-based skateboard rental platform that enables users to browse available skateboards, reserve them for specific time periods, complete rentals, and return equipment. The system manages inventory, user accounts, rental transactions, and return processing.

### 1.2 Goals
- Provide a seamless user experience for booking and returning skateboards
- Manage skateboard inventory and availability in real-time
- Track rental history and user statistics
- Generate revenue reports and operational insights
- Minimize skateboard losses and damage through tracking

### 1.3 Target Users
- Casual riders seeking short-term skateboard access
- Skateboard enthusiasts testing different equipment
- Tourists in urban areas
- Riders without personal equipment

---

## 2. User Roles and Personas

### 2.1 Customer
- **Description**: Primary user renting skateboards
- **Goals**: Find, rent, and return skateboards with minimal friction
- **Technical Level**: General public

### 2.2 Admin
- **Description**: System operator managing inventory and disputes
- **Goals**: Monitor system health, manage inventory, resolve issues
- **Technical Level**: Intermediate

### 2.3 Support Staff
- **Description**: Handles customer inquiries and damage claims
- **Goals**: Resolve customer issues, process returns, manage complaints
- **Technical Level**: Intermediate

---

## 3. Core Features

### 3.1 User Management
- User registration with email verification
- Profile creation (name, phone, address, payment method)
- Password reset and account recovery
- User authentication (JWT tokens with 24-hour expiration)
- Account suspension and reactivation

### 3.2 Skateboard Inventory
- Add/edit skateboard details (brand, model, condition, features)
- Track skateboard location (rental center, in-use, maintenance)
- Condition assessment (new, good, fair, needs repair)
- Categorize by type (street, cruiser, longboard, electric)
- Upload skateboard images and specifications

### 3.3 Rental Management
- Search and filter available skateboards by type, features, location
- Reserve skateboard for specific date and time range
- Checkout process with rental agreement acceptance
- Dynamic pricing based on duration and demand
- Support for hourly, daily, and weekly rental periods
- Automatic rental expiration notifications
- Late return penalties calculation

### 3.4 Return Processing
- Return check-in at designated locations
- Condition assessment at return
- Damage documentation with photo evidence
- Return location flexibility (same/different location option)
- Automatic deposit refund for undamaged returns
- Damage claim processing workflow

### 3.5 Payment Processing
- Support credit/debit card payments
- Digital wallet integration (PayPal, Apple Pay, Google Pay)
- Security deposit requirement (refundable)
- Rental fee calculation and invoicing
- Damage charge processing
- Late fee calculation and charging
- Payment receipt generation and email delivery

### 3.6 User Dashboard
- Rental history with filtering and search
- Active rental status and countdown timer
- Upcoming reservations
- Account settings and payment methods
- Damage claim history
- Rating and review submission for rentals

### 3.7 Admin Dashboard
- Real-time inventory status
- Rental and revenue analytics
- User management and account moderation
- Damage claim review and resolution
- System health monitoring
- Report generation (daily, weekly, monthly)

