## 4. User Stories with Acceptance Criteria

### 4.1 User Registration
**Story**: As a new user, I want to register an account so I can rent skateboards

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- User can enter email, password, and confirm password
- System validates email format and password strength (min 8 chars, 1 uppercase, 1 number, 1 special char)
- Email verification link sent within 60 seconds
- Account created after email verification
- Error messages displayed for invalid input
- Registration completes in under 2 minutes total
- Success message confirms account creation

### 4.2 Skateboard Search
**Story**: As a customer, I want to search and filter available skateboards so I can find the right one for my needs

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- Filter by skateboard type, features, rental period, location
- Results show in under 500ms
- Search results display with images, features, price, and availability
- Can sort by price (low-to-high, high-to-low), newest, rating
- Real-time availability status displayed
- Show 10 results per page with pagination
- Mobile-responsive layout

### 4.3 Rental Booking
**Story**: As a customer, I want to book a skateboard for a specific time period so I can use it when I need it

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- Select date and time for pickup and return
- System prevents booking past return dates
- Dynamic price calculation displayed before confirmation
- Rental agreement summary shown for review
- One-click acceptance of rental agreement
- Confirmation email sent with rental details and pickup instructions
- Booking confirmation contains QR code for check-in
- Payment captured immediately upon confirmation
- Booking reference provided for check-in

### 4.4 Skateboard Check-in
**Story**: As a customer, I want to check out my rented skateboard so I can start using it

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- QR code scan or manual code entry enables check-in
- Identity verification required (last 4 of phone or ID)
- Condition assessment form presented before release
- Customer confirms received condition matches listed condition
- Rental countdown timer starts
- Return location and deadline clearly displayed
- SMS reminder sent at checkout with return deadline

### 4.5 Skateboard Return
**Story**: As a customer, I want to return my skateboard so I can end the rental

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- Return at any designated location during operating hours
- QR code scan initiates return process
- Condition assessment performed by staff
- Photos taken if damage detected
- Damage charges calculated and displayed immediately
- Deposit refund processed within 24 hours for undamaged returns
- Return receipt emailed with final charges
- Rental completion recorded in history

### 4.6 Late Return Handling
**Story**: As a customer renting beyond the agreed time, I want to be notified and charged appropriately

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- SMS/email reminder at 1 hour before deadline
- Late fees applied at $5 per hour after deadline
- Maximum daily late fee capped at 50% of daily rental cost
- Grace period of 15 minutes before fees apply
- Customer notified of accumulated charges
- Charges applied at return check-in
- Invoice shows itemized breakdown

### 4.7 Damage Claim Processing
**Story**: As support staff, I want to document and process damage claims so disputes are resolved fairly

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- Damage photos and description captured at return
- Damage severity assessed (minor, moderate, major)
- Repair/replacement cost estimated
- Customer notified within 24 hours of claim
- Appeals process available for 7 days
- Funds deducted from deposit or charged to payment method
- Claim resolution documented in system
- Closed claims archived with full documentation

### 4.8 Admin Analytics Dashboard
**Story**: As an admin, I want to view system analytics so I can understand business performance

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- Dashboard loads within 2 seconds
- Display total revenue, rentals, and active users (current period)
- Charts show revenue trends (daily, weekly, monthly options)
- Equipment utilization rates by skateboard type
- Top-rented locations identified
- Damage rate analysis with top damaged models
- User growth metrics
- Peak rental times identified
- Export reports as PDF or CSV

